<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-163-069 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 771 347</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Learning  May-June 1991 v10 n8 p56(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Challenging students to learn. (how educator Gail Morse teachersher students to use technology)</TITLE><AUTHOR>November, Alan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Educator Gail Morse is adept at helping her students learn to usetechnology in the classroom.andP;  Because she lacks the time toinstruct about technologies on an individual level, Morse stressescommunication methods to get students to work in teams and tostress self-learning.andP;  The teams then divide up to tackle varioustechnologies and to apply their knowledge for the good of theclass as a whole.andP;  Sample technology teams include atelecommunications team that learns how to use various computernetworks and provides library research, a VCR team that uses acamcorder to develop a video yearbook, and a computer team thatshow others how to use numerous computer applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     EducationTechnology.andO;Feature:   illustrationcartoon.andO;Person:    Morse, Gail (Education policy).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>